{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Albone Glacier | other_name = | photo = Ant-pen-map-Nordenskjöld.PNG | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Location of Nordenskjöld Coast | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Albone Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[Graham Land]] | coordinates = {{coord|64|13|S|59|42|W|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = | width = | thickness = | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Nordenskjöld Coast]] | status = | embedded = }}
'''Albone Glacier''' ({{coord|64|13|S|59|42|W|type:glacier_region:AQ|display=inline,title}}) is a deeply entrenched narrow [[glacier]] on the east side of [[Wolseley Buttress]] flowing southward from [[Detroit Plateau]] on [[Nordenskjöld Coast]] in [[Graham Land]], [[Antarctica]]. It was mapped by the [[Falkland Islands Dependencies Survey]] from surveys (1960&ndash;61) and was named by the [[United Kingdom Antarctic Place-Names Committee]] for [[Dan Albone]], English designer of the Ivel tractor, the first successful [[tractor]] with an internal combustion engine.
