The '''Artemis Chasma''' is the nearly circular fracture in [[Venus]]'s surface which almost encloses [[Artemis Corona]]. The [[chasma]] and its associating [[Corona (planetary geology)|corona]] can be found on the [[Aphrodite Terra]] continent, at Latitude 35° South, Longitude 135° East.

It is named after the [[Artemis]], the [[Greek mythology|Greek]] virgin goddess of the hunt and the moon, the hills, the forest, birth, virginity, and fertility, who carries a bow and arrow.

