'''Malus''' ([[Latin]] for ''[[mast (sailing)|mast]]'') was a subdivision of the ancient [[constellation]] [[Argo Navis]] proposed in 1844 by the English astronomer John Herschel. It would have replaced [[Pyxis]], the compass, which was introduced in the 1750s by Nicolas Louis de [[Lacaille]]. Herschel's suggestion was not widely adopted and Malus is not now recognized by astronomers.

