'''Multipartite''' is a class of [[virus]] that have segmented nucleic acid genomes. Only a few [[ssDNA]] viruses have multipartite genomes, but a lot more RNA viruses have multipartite genomes.<ref>http://www.ndsu.edu/pubweb/~mcclean/plsc411/viral-genome-structures-lecture-and-overheads.pdf</ref> An advantage of multipartite genome is its ability to synthesize multiple [[mRNA]] strands to avoid the cellular constraint of [[monocistronic|monocistronicity]].
