{{unreferenced|date=February 2011}}
'''Silvano Canzoneri''' (4 February 1941 in [[Corleone]] &ndash; 5 October 1995 in [[Venice]]) was an [[Italians|Italian]] [[entomologist]].

Canzoneri specialized in [[Coleoptera]], especially [[Tenebrionidae]], [[Diptera]] and [[Ephydridae]].

==References==
*[http://www.coleoptera.org/p1712.htm Coleoptera org] In Italian includes full bibliography and list of [[taxa]] described by him.


